President Trump announced that the FDA is working with the private sector to eliminate outdated rules and bureaucracy in order to accelerate progress in combating the Coronavirus. The FDA is committed to providing regulatory flexibility and guidance while ensuring product safety and effectiveness. Clinical trials for antiviral therapies are already underway, and one existing treatment, Chloroquine and its derivative Hydroxychloroquine, will soon be available for many patients to try. The President also signed the Family First bill, providing support for workers, small businesses, and families. Vice President Pence announced that tens of thousands of tests are being performed daily, and access to medical equipment is being expanded. First Lady Melania Trump offered encouragement, stating that the current situation is temporary and normalcy will return. It is important to stay connected with loved ones using technology and follow CDC guidelines.